      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DOUBLE FEAR (4) was brave at this circuit and distance last week when he raced parked from this barrier and fought well to go under by just a head as runner-up. Stays in the same grade and with a touch better luck could go one better. CASH AND BLING (3) backs up after adding to a string of close up efforts when coming from wider to be beaten 4m into fourth in a higher-graded race on Saturday. Hart to goes on and has won two of four drives on him. Should enjoy a nice run so looks a danger. FOXY DADA (5) should strip fitter and must be considered after he finished third when resuming at Bankstown last week. ULTIMATE BIRD NZ (8) draws wide but has been solid in two starts since a spell and is building in fitness.",
